definition: to do/to grow/to write or compose/to pretend/to regard as/to feel/writings or works

sentences.english: The next paper from one side of this test for further exploration.
sentences.chinese: 接下来本文就从一个侧面对此试作进一步探讨。

sentences.english: The few surviving scraps of notes are crammed with story tentatives .
sentences.chinese: 所留存的一些零碎笔记满是故事的试作。

sentences.english: This paper tries to correct some of these errors in this book.
sentences.chinese: 本文仅就其中的一些失误试作匡正。
爱潘妮试作最后的努力。

sentences.english: Only a few sample pieces were struck, which never entered circulation.
sentences.chinese: 仅试作数枚，没有进入流通。

sentences.english: His first attempt at English composition was poor.
sentences.chinese: 他初次试作的英语作文很糟糕。

sentences.english: Further more, this course can help students to simulate self planning career ladder for further selection and preparation of jobs.
sentences.chinese: 进而试作自我之生涯规划，为择业与工作之准备。

sentences.english: The first throw quad salchow Shen Xue and Zhao Hongbo attempted was flawless.
sentences.chinese: 申雪和越宏博试作的和一个四周抛跳完美无瑕。

sentences.english: This paper tries to explore the images of the oriental culture in The Love Poems of Marichiko.
sentences.chinese: 本文对《摩利支子情诗》中的东方文化意象试作探讨。

sentences.english: This article on vocal music teaching in esthetic question test shallow exploration.
sentences.chinese: 本文就声乐教学中的审美化问题试作粗浅探索。

definition: lit. a brick thrown to prompt others to produce a jade (idiom)/fig. a modest suggestion intended to prompt others to come forward with better ideas
to do/to grow/to write or compose/to pretend/to regard as/to feel/writings or works
to venture to/to presume to/to take the liberty of
in order to minimally fulfill one's responsibilities/in order to get off the hook
my unworthy manuscript (humble expr.)/my humble writing
to trace over/to copy (a calligraphy model)/facsimile/(fig.) to depict/to portray
some cases picked out as example/to highlight
to move the pen/to start writing/putting pen to paper
